63static void
64tkey_log(const char *fmt, ...) ISC_FORMAT_PRINTF(1, 2);

66static void
67tkey_log(const char *fmt, ...) {
68 va_list ap;
69
70 va_start(ap, fmt);
71 isc_log_vwrite(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_GENERAL,
72 DNS_LOGMODULE_REQUEST, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(4), fmt, ap);
73 va_end(ap);
74}

76static void
77dumpmessage(dns_message_t *msg) {
78 isc_buffer_t outbuf;
79 unsigned char *output;
80 int len = TEMP_BUFFER_SZ;
81 isc_result_t result;
82
83 for (;;) {
84 output = isc_mem_get(msg->mctx, len);
85 if (output == NULL)
86 return;
87
88 isc_buffer_init(&outbuf, output, len);
89 result = dns_message_totext(msg, &dns_master_style_debug,
90 0, &outbuf);
91 if (result == ISC_R_NOSPACE) {
92 isc_mem_put(msg->mctx, output, len);
93 len *= 2;
94 continue;
95 }
96
97 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
98 tkey_log("%.*s",
99 (int)isc_buffer_usedlength(&outbuf),
100 (char *)isc_buffer_base(&outbuf));
101 else
102 tkey_log("Warning: dns_message_totext: %s",
103 dns_result_totext(result));
104 break;
105 }
106
107 if (output != NULL)
108 isc_mem_put(msg->mctx, output, len);
109}

111isc_result_t
112dns_tkeyctx_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_tkeyctx_t **tctxp)
113{
114 dns_tkeyctx_t *tctx;
115
116 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
117 REQUIRE(tctxp != NULL && *tctxp == NULL);
118
119 tctx = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_tkeyctx_t));
120 if (tctx == NULL)
121 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
122 tctx->mctx = NULL;
123 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &tctx->mctx);
124 tctx->dhkey = NULL;
125 tctx->domain = NULL;
126 tctx->gsscred = NULL;
127 tctx->gssapi_keytab = NULL;
128
129 *tctxp = tctx;
130 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
131}
132
133void
134dns_tkeyctx_destroy(dns_tkeyctx_t **tctxp) {
135 isc_mem_t *mctx;
136 dns_tkeyctx_t *tctx;
137
138 REQUIRE(tctxp != NULL && *tctxp != NULL);
139
140 tctx = *tctxp;
141 mctx = tctx->mctx;
142
143 if (tctx->dhkey != NULL)
144 dst_key_free(&tctx->dhkey);
145 if (tctx->domain != NULL) {
146 if (dns_name_dynamic(tctx->domain))
147 dns_name_free(tctx->domain, mctx);
148 isc_mem_put(mctx, tctx->domain, sizeof(dns_name_t));
149 }
150 if (tctx->gssapi_keytab != NULL) {
151 isc_mem_free(mctx, tctx->gssapi_keytab);
152 }
153 if (tctx->gsscred != NULL)
154 dst_gssapi_releasecred(&tctx->gsscred);
155 isc_mem_put(mctx, tctx, sizeof(dns_tkeyctx_t));
156 isc_mem_detach(&mctx);
157 *tctxp = NULL;
158}

160static isc_result_t
161add_rdata_to_list(dns_message_t *msg, dns_name_t *name, dns_rdata_t *rdata,
162 uint32_t ttl, dns_namelist_t *namelist)
163{
164 isc_result_t result;
165 isc_region_t r, newr;
166 dns_rdata_t *newrdata = NULL;
167 dns_name_t *newname = NULL;
168 dns_rdatalist_t *newlist = NULL;
169 dns_rdataset_t *newset = NULL;
170 isc_buffer_t *tmprdatabuf = NULL;
171
172 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdata(msg, &newrdata));
173
174 dns_rdata_toregion(rdata, &r);
175 RETERR(isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &tmprdatabuf, r.length));
176 isc_buffer_availableregion(tmprdatabuf, &newr);
177 memmove(newr.base, r.base, r.length);
178 dns_rdata_fromregion(newrdata, rdata->rdclass, rdata->type, &newr);
179 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &tmprdatabuf);
180
181 RETERR(dns_message_gettempname(msg, &newname));
182 dns_name_init(newname, NULL);
183 RETERR(dns_name_dup(name, msg->mctx, newname));
184
185 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdatalist(msg, &newlist));
186 newlist->rdclass = newrdata->rdclass;
187 newlist->type = newrdata->type;
188 newlist->ttl = ttl;
189 ISC_LIST_APPEND(newlist->rdata, newrdata, link);
190
191 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg, &newset));
192 RETERR(dns_rdatalist_tordataset(newlist, newset));
193
194 ISC_LIST_INIT(newname->list);
195 ISC_LIST_APPEND(newname->list, newset, link);
196
197 ISC_LIST_APPEND(*namelist, newname, link);
198
199 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
200
201 failure:
202 if (newrdata != NULL) {
203 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(newrdata, link)) {
204 INSIST(newlist != NULL);
205 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(newlist->rdata, newrdata, link);
206 }
207 dns_message_puttemprdata(msg, &newrdata);
208 }
209 if (newname != NULL)
210 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &newname);
211 if (newset != NULL) {
212 dns_rdataset_disassociate(newset);
213 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg, &newset);
214 }
215 if (newlist != NULL)
216 dns_message_puttemprdatalist(msg, &newlist);
217 return (result);
218}
219
220static void
221free_namelist(dns_message_t *msg, dns_namelist_t *namelist) {
222 dns_name_t *name;
223 dns_rdataset_t *set;
224
225 while (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(*namelist)) {
226 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(*namelist);
227 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(*namelist, name, link);
228 while (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(name->list)) {
229 set = ISC_LIST_HEAD(name->list);
230 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(name->list, set, link);
231 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg, &set);
232 }
233 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &name);
234 }
235}

237static isc_result_t
238compute_secret(isc_buffer_t *shared, isc_region_t *queryrandomness,
239 isc_region_t *serverrandomness, isc_buffer_t *secret)
240{
241 isc_md_t *md;
242 isc_region_t r, r2;
243 unsigned char digests[ISC_MAX_MD_SIZE*2];
244 unsigned char *digest1, *digest2;
245 unsigned int digestslen, digestlen1 = 0, digestlen2 = 0;
246 unsigned int i;
247 isc_result_t result;
248
249 isc_buffer_usedregion(shared, &r);
250
251 md = isc_md_new();
252 if (md == NULL) {
253 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
254 }
255
256 /*
257 * MD5 ( query data | DH value ).
258 */
259 digest1 = digests;
260
261 result = isc_md_init(md, ISC_MD_MD5);
262 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
263 goto end;
264 }
265
266 result = isc_md_update(md,
267 queryrandomness->base,
268 queryrandomness->length);
269 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
270 goto end;
271 }
272
273 result = isc_md_update(md, r.base, r.length);
274 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
275 goto end;
276 }
277
278 result = isc_md_final(md, digest1, &digestlen1);
279 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
280 goto end;
281 }
282
283 result = isc_md_reset(md);
284 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
285 goto end;
286 }
287
288 /*
289 * MD5 ( server data | DH value ).
290 */
291 digest2 = digests + digestlen1;
292
293 result = isc_md_init(md, ISC_MD_MD5);
294 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
295 goto end;
296 }
297
298 result = isc_md_update(md,
299 serverrandomness->base,
300 serverrandomness->length);
301 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
302 goto end;
303 }
304
305 result = isc_md_update(md, r.base, r.length);
306 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
307 goto end;
308 }
309
310 result = isc_md_final(md, digest2, &digestlen2);
311 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
312 goto end;
313 }
314
315 isc_md_free(md);
316 md = NULL;
317
318 digestslen = digestlen1 + digestlen2;
319
320 /*
321 * XOR ( DH value, MD5-1 | MD5-2).
322 */
323 isc_buffer_availableregion(secret, &r);
324 isc_buffer_usedregion(shared, &r2);
325 if (r.length < digestslen || r.length < r2.length) {
326 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
327 }
328 if (r2.length > digestslen) {
329 memmove(r.base, r2.base, r2.length);
330 for (i = 0; i < digestslen; i++) {
331 r.base[i] ^= digests[i];
332 }
333 isc_buffer_add(secret, r2.length);
334 } else {
335 memmove(r.base, digests, digestslen);
336 for (i = 0; i < r2.length; i++) {
337 r.base[i] ^= r2.base[i];
338 }
339 isc_buffer_add(secret, digestslen);
340 }
341 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
342end:
343 if (md != NULL) {
344 isc_md_free(md);
345 }
346 return (result);
347}

349static isc_result_t
350process_dhtkey(dns_message_t *msg, dns_name_t *signer, dns_name_t *name,
351 dns_rdata_tkey_t *tkeyin, dns_tkeyctx_t *tctx,
352 dns_rdata_tkey_t *tkeyout,
353 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring, dns_namelist_t *namelist)
354{
355 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
356 dns_name_t *keyname, ourname;
357 dns_rdataset_t *keyset = NULL;
358 dns_rdata_t keyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT, ourkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
359 bool found_key = false, found_incompatible = false;
360 dst_key_t *pubkey = NULL;
361 isc_buffer_t ourkeybuf, *shared = NULL;
362 isc_region_t r, r2, ourkeyr;
363 unsigned char keydata[DST_KEY_MAXSIZE];
364 unsigned int sharedsize;
365 isc_buffer_t secret;
366 unsigned char *randomdata = NULL, secretdata[256];
367 dns_ttl_t ttl = 0;
368
369 if (tctx->dhkey == NULL) {
370 tkey_log("process_dhtkey: tkey-dhkey not defined");
371 tkeyout->error = dns_tsigerror_badalg;
372 return (DNS_R_REFUSED);
373 }
374
375 if (!dns_name_equal(&tkeyin->algorithm, DNS_TSIG_HMACMD5_NAME)) {
376 tkey_log("process_dhtkey: algorithms other than "
377 "hmac-md5 are not supported");
378 tkeyout->error = dns_tsigerror_badalg;
379 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
380 }
381
382 /*
383 * Look for a DH KEY record that will work with ours.
384 */
385 for (result = dns_message_firstname(msg, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL);
386 result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && !found_key;
387 result = dns_message_nextname(msg, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL)) {
388 keyname = NULL;
389 dns_message_currentname(msg, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL, &keyname);
390 keyset = NULL;
391 result = dns_message_findtype(keyname, dns_rdatatype_key, 0,
392 &keyset);
393 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
394 continue;
395
396 for (result = dns_rdataset_first(keyset);
397 result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && !found_key;
398 result = dns_rdataset_next(keyset)) {
399 dns_rdataset_current(keyset, &keyrdata);
400 pubkey = NULL;
401 result = dns_dnssec_keyfromrdata(keyname, &keyrdata,
402 msg->mctx, &pubkey);
403 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
404 dns_rdata_reset(&keyrdata);
405 continue;
406 }
407 if (dst_key_alg(pubkey) == DNS_KEYALG_DH) {
408 if (dst_key_paramcompare(pubkey, tctx->dhkey))
409 {
410 found_key = true;
411 ttl = keyset->ttl;
412 break;
413 } else
414 found_incompatible = true;
415 }
416 dst_key_free(&pubkey);
417 dns_rdata_reset(&keyrdata);
418 }
419 }
420
421 if (!found_key) {
422 if (found_incompatible) {
423 tkey_log("process_dhtkey: found an incompatible key");
424 tkeyout->error = dns_tsigerror_badkey;
425 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
426 } else {
427 tkey_log("process_dhtkey: failed to find a key");
428 return (DNS_R_FORMERR);
429 }
430 }
431
432 RETERR(add_rdata_to_list(msg, keyname, &keyrdata, ttl, namelist));
433
434 isc_buffer_init(&ourkeybuf, keydata, sizeof(keydata));
435 RETERR(dst_key_todns(tctx->dhkey, &ourkeybuf));
436 isc_buffer_usedregion(&ourkeybuf, &ourkeyr);
437 dns_rdata_fromregion(&ourkeyrdata, dns_rdataclass_any,
438 dns_rdatatype_key, &ourkeyr);
439
440 dns_name_init(&ourname, NULL);
441 dns_name_clone(dst_key_name(tctx->dhkey), &ourname);
442
443 /*
444 * XXXBEW The TTL should be obtained from the database, if it exists.
445 */
446 RETERR(add_rdata_to_list(msg, &ourname, &ourkeyrdata, 0, namelist));
447
448 RETERR(dst_key_secretsize(tctx->dhkey, &sharedsize));
449 RETERR(isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &shared, sharedsize));
450
451 result = dst_key_computesecret(pubkey, tctx->dhkey, shared);
452 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
453 tkey_log("process_dhtkey: failed to compute shared secret: %s",
454 isc_result_totext(result));
455 goto failure;
456 }
457 dst_key_free(&pubkey);
458
459 isc_buffer_init(&secret, secretdata, sizeof(secretdata));
460
461 randomdata = isc_mem_get(tkeyout->mctx, TKEY_RANDOM_AMOUNT);
462 if (randomdata == NULL)
463 goto failure;
464
465 isc_nonce_buf(randomdata, TKEY_RANDOM_AMOUNT);
466
467 r.base = randomdata;
468 r.length = TKEY_RANDOM_AMOUNT;
469 r2.base = tkeyin->key;
470 r2.length = tkeyin->keylen;
471 RETERR(compute_secret(shared, &r2, &r, &secret));
472 isc_buffer_free(&shared);
473
474 RETERR(dns_tsigkey_create(name, &tkeyin->algorithm,
475 isc_buffer_base(&secret),
476 isc_buffer_usedlength(&secret),
477 true, signer, tkeyin->inception,
478 tkeyin->expire, ring->mctx, ring, NULL));
479
480 /* This key is good for a long time */
481 tkeyout->inception = tkeyin->inception;
482 tkeyout->expire = tkeyin->expire;
483
484 tkeyout->key = randomdata;
485 tkeyout->keylen = TKEY_RANDOM_AMOUNT;
486
487 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
488
489 failure:
490 if (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(*namelist))
491 free_namelist(msg, namelist);
492 if (shared != NULL)
493 isc_buffer_free(&shared);
494 if (pubkey != NULL)
495 dst_key_free(&pubkey);
496 if (randomdata != NULL)
497 isc_mem_put(tkeyout->mctx, randomdata, TKEY_RANDOM_AMOUNT);
498 return (result);
499}

501static isc_result_t
502process_gsstkey(dns_message_t *msg, dns_name_t *name, dns_rdata_tkey_t *tkeyin,
503 dns_tkeyctx_t *tctx, dns_rdata_tkey_t *tkeyout,
504 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring)
505{
506 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
507 dst_key_t *dstkey = NULL;
508 dns_tsigkey_t *tsigkey = NULL;
509 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
510 dns_name_t *principal;
511 isc_stdtime_t now;
512 isc_region_t intoken;
513 isc_buffer_t *outtoken = NULL;
514 gss_ctx_id_t gss_ctx = NULL;
515
516 /*
517 * You have to define either a gss credential (principal) to
518 * accept with tkey-gssapi-credential, or you have to
519 * configure a specific keytab (with tkey-gssapi-keytab) in
520 * order to use gsstkey.
521 */
522 if (tctx->gsscred == NULL && tctx->gssapi_keytab == NULL) {
523 tkey_log("process_gsstkey(): no tkey-gssapi-credential "
524 "or tkey-gssapi-keytab configured");
525 return (ISC_R_NOPERM);
526 }
527
528 if (!dns_name_equal(&tkeyin->algorithm, DNS_TSIG_GSSAPI_NAME) &&
529 !dns_name_equal(&tkeyin->algorithm, DNS_TSIG_GSSAPIMS_NAME)) {
530 tkeyout->error = dns_tsigerror_badalg;
531 tkey_log("process_gsstkey(): dns_tsigerror_badalg"); /* XXXSRA */
532 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
533 }
534
535 /*
536 * XXXDCL need to check for key expiry per 4.1.1
537 * XXXDCL need a way to check fully established, perhaps w/key_flags
538 */
539
540 intoken.base = tkeyin->key;
541 intoken.length = tkeyin->keylen;
542
543 result = dns_tsigkey_find(&tsigkey, name, &tkeyin->algorithm, ring);
544 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
545 gss_ctx = dst_key_getgssctx(tsigkey->key);
546
547 principal = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
548
549 /*
550 * Note that tctx->gsscred may be NULL if tctx->gssapi_keytab is set
551 */
552 result = dst_gssapi_acceptctx(tctx->gsscred, tctx->gssapi_keytab,
553 &intoken, &outtoken, &gss_ctx,
554 principal, tctx->mctx);
555 if (result == DNS_R_INVALIDTKEY) {
556 if (tsigkey != NULL)
557 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
558 tkeyout->error = dns_tsigerror_badkey;
559 tkey_log("process_gsstkey(): dns_tsigerror_badkey"); /* XXXSRA */
560 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
561 }
562 if (result != DNS_R_CONTINUE && result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
563 goto failure;
564 /*
565 * XXXDCL Section 4.1.3: Limit GSS_S_CONTINUE_NEEDED to 10 times.
566 */
567
568 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
569
570 if (dns_name_countlabels(principal) == 0U) {
571 if (tsigkey != NULL) {
572 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
573 }
574 } else if (tsigkey == NULL) {
575#ifdef GSSAPI
576 OM_uint32 gret, minor, lifetime;
577#endif
578 uint32_t expire;
579
580 RETERR(dst_key_fromgssapi(name, gss_ctx, ring->mctx,
581 &dstkey, &intoken));
582 /*
583 * Limit keys to 1 hour or the context's lifetime whichever
584 * is smaller.
585 */
586 expire = now + 3600;
587#ifdef GSSAPI
588 gret = gss_context_time(&minor, gss_ctx, &lifetime);
589 if (gret == GSS_S_COMPLETE && now + lifetime < expire)
590 expire = now + lifetime;
591#endif
592 RETERR(dns_tsigkey_createfromkey(name, &tkeyin->algorithm,
593 dstkey, true, principal,
594 now, expire, ring->mctx, ring,
595 &tsigkey));
596 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
597 tkeyout->inception = now;
598 tkeyout->expire = expire;
599 } else {
600 tkeyout->inception = tsigkey->inception;
601 tkeyout->expire = tsigkey->expire;
602 }
603
604 if (outtoken) {
605 tkeyout->key = isc_mem_get(tkeyout->mctx,
606 isc_buffer_usedlength(outtoken));
607 if (tkeyout->key == NULL) {
608 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
609 goto failure;
610 }
611 tkeyout->keylen = isc_buffer_usedlength(outtoken);
612 memmove(tkeyout->key, isc_buffer_base(outtoken),
613 isc_buffer_usedlength(outtoken));
614 isc_buffer_free(&outtoken);
615 } else {
616 tkeyout->key = isc_mem_get(tkeyout->mctx, tkeyin->keylen);
617 if (tkeyout->key == NULL) {
618 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
619 goto failure;
620 }
621 tkeyout->keylen = tkeyin->keylen;
622 memmove(tkeyout->key, tkeyin->key, tkeyin->keylen);
623 }
624
625 tkeyout->error = dns_rcode_noerror;
626
627 tkey_log("process_gsstkey(): dns_tsigerror_noerror"); /* XXXSRA */
628
629 /*
630 * We found a TKEY to respond with. If the request is not TSIG signed,
631 * we need to make sure the response is signed (see RFC 3645, Section
632 * 2.2).
633 */
634 if (tsigkey != NULL) {
635 if (msg->tsigkey == NULL && msg->sig0key == NULL) {
636 dns_message_settsigkey(msg, tsigkey);
637 }
638 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
639 }
640
641 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
642
643failure:
644 if (tsigkey != NULL)
645 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
646
647 if (dstkey != NULL)
648 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
649
650 if (outtoken != NULL)
651 isc_buffer_free(&outtoken);
652
653 tkey_log("process_gsstkey(): %s",
654 isc_result_totext(result)); /* XXXSRA */
655
656 return (result);
657}

659static isc_result_t
660process_deletetkey(dns_name_t *signer, dns_name_t *name,
661 dns_rdata_tkey_t *tkeyin, dns_rdata_tkey_t *tkeyout,
662 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring)
663{
664 isc_result_t result;
665 dns_tsigkey_t *tsigkey = NULL;
666 dns_name_t *identity;
667
668 result = dns_tsigkey_find(&tsigkey, name, &tkeyin->algorithm, ring);
669 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
670 tkeyout->error = dns_tsigerror_badname;
671 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
672 }
673
674 /*
675 * Only allow a delete if the identity that created the key is the
676 * same as the identity that signed the message.
677 */
678 identity = dns_tsigkey_identity(tsigkey);
679 if (identity == NULL || !dns_name_equal(identity, signer)) {
680 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
681 return (DNS_R_REFUSED);
682 }
683
684 /*
685 * Set the key to be deleted when no references are left. If the key
686 * was not generated with TKEY and is in the config file, it may be
687 * reloaded later.
688 */
689 dns_tsigkey_setdeleted(tsigkey);
690
691 /* Release the reference */
692 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
693
694 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
695}
696
697isc_result_t
698dns_tkey_processquery(dns_message_t *msg, dns_tkeyctx_t *tctx,
699 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring)
700{
701 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
702 dns_rdata_tkey_t tkeyin, tkeyout;
703 bool freetkeyin = false;
704 dns_name_t *qname, *name, *keyname, *signer, tsigner;
705 dns_fixedname_t fkeyname;
706 dns_rdataset_t *tkeyset;
707 dns_rdata_t rdata;
708 dns_namelist_t namelist;
709 char tkeyoutdata[512];
710 isc_buffer_t tkeyoutbuf;
711
712 REQUIRE(msg != NULL);
713 REQUIRE(tctx != NULL);
714 REQUIRE(ring != NULL);
715
716 ISC_LIST_INIT(namelist);
717
718 /*
719 * Interpret the question section.
720 */
721 result = dns_message_firstname(msg, DNS_SECTION_QUESTION);
722 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
723 return (DNS_R_FORMERR);
724
725 qname = NULL;
726 dns_message_currentname(msg, DNS_SECTION_QUESTION, &qname);
727
728 /*
729 * Look for a TKEY record that matches the question.
730 */
731 tkeyset = NULL;
732 name = NULL;
733 result = dns_message_findname(msg, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL, qname,
734 dns_rdatatype_tkey, 0, &name, &tkeyset);
735 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
736 /*
737 * Try the answer section, since that's where Win2000
738 * puts it.
739 */
740 name = NULL;
741 if (dns_message_findname(msg, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER, qname,
742 dns_rdatatype_tkey, 0, &name,
743 &tkeyset) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
744 result = DNS_R_FORMERR;
745 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processquery: couldn't find a TKEY "
746 "matching the question");
747 goto failure;
748 }
749 }
750 result = dns_rdataset_first(tkeyset);
751 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
752 result = DNS_R_FORMERR;
753 goto failure;
754 }
755 dns_rdata_init(&rdata);
756 dns_rdataset_current(tkeyset, &rdata);
757
758 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &tkeyin, NULL));
759 freetkeyin = true;
760
761 if (tkeyin.error != dns_rcode_noerror) {
762 result = DNS_R_FORMERR;
763 goto failure;
764 }
765
766 /*
767 * Before we go any farther, verify that the message was signed.
768 * GSSAPI TKEY doesn't require a signature, the rest do.
769 */
770 dns_name_init(&tsigner, NULL);
771 result = dns_message_signer(msg, &tsigner);
772 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
773 if (tkeyin.mode == DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI &&
774 result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
775 signer = NULL;
776 } else {
777 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processquery: query was not "
778 "properly signed - rejecting");
779 result = DNS_R_FORMERR;
780 goto failure;
781 }
782 } else
783 signer = &tsigner;
784
785 tkeyout.common.rdclass = tkeyin.common.rdclass;
786 tkeyout.common.rdtype = tkeyin.common.rdtype;
787 ISC_LINK_INIT(&tkeyout.common, link);
788 tkeyout.mctx = msg->mctx;
789
790 dns_name_init(&tkeyout.algorithm, NULL);
791 dns_name_clone(&tkeyin.algorithm, &tkeyout.algorithm);
792
793 tkeyout.inception = tkeyout.expire = 0;
794 tkeyout.mode = tkeyin.mode;
795 tkeyout.error = 0;
796 tkeyout.keylen = tkeyout.otherlen = 0;
797 tkeyout.key = tkeyout.other = NULL;
798
799 /*
800 * A delete operation must have a fully specified key name. If this
801 * is not a delete, we do the following:
802 * if (qname != ".")
803 * keyname = qname + defaultdomain
804 * else
805 * keyname = <random hex> + defaultdomain
806 */
807 if (tkeyin.mode != DNS_TKEYMODE_DELETE) {
808 dns_tsigkey_t *tsigkey = NULL;
809
810 if (tctx->domain == NULL && tkeyin.mode != DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI) {
811 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processquery: tkey-domain not set");
812 result = DNS_R_REFUSED;
813 goto failure;
814 }
815
816 keyname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fkeyname);
817
818 if (!dns_name_equal(qname, dns_rootname)) {
819 unsigned int n = dns_name_countlabels(qname);
820 RUNTIME_CHECK(dns_name_copy(qname, keyname, NULL)
821 == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
822 dns_name_getlabelsequence(keyname, 0, n - 1, keyname);
823 } else {
824 static char hexdigits[16] = {
825 '0', '1', '2', '3', '4', '5', '6', '7',
826 '8', '9', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F' };
827 unsigned char randomdata[16];
828 char randomtext[32];
829 isc_buffer_t b;
830 unsigned int i, j;
831
832 isc_nonce_buf(randomdata, sizeof(randomdata));
833
834 for (i = 0, j = 0; i < sizeof(randomdata); i++) {
835 unsigned char val = randomdata[i];
836 randomtext[j++] = hexdigits[val >> 4];
837 randomtext[j++] = hexdigits[val & 0xF];
838 }
839 isc_buffer_init(&b, randomtext, sizeof(randomtext));
840 isc_buffer_add(&b, sizeof(randomtext));
841 result = dns_name_fromtext(keyname, &b, NULL, 0, NULL);
842 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
843 goto failure;
844 }
845
846 if (tkeyin.mode == DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI) {
847 /* Yup. This is a hack */
848 result = dns_name_concatenate(keyname, dns_rootname,
849 keyname, NULL);
850 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
851 goto failure;
852 } else {
853 result = dns_name_concatenate(keyname, tctx->domain,
854 keyname, NULL);
855 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
856 goto failure;
857 }
858
859 result = dns_tsigkey_find(&tsigkey, keyname, NULL, ring);
860
861 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
862 tkeyout.error = dns_tsigerror_badname;
863 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
864 goto failure_with_tkey;
865 } else if (result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
866 goto failure;
867 } else
868 keyname = qname;
869
870 switch (tkeyin.mode) {
871 case DNS_TKEYMODE_DIFFIEHELLMAN:
872 tkeyout.error = dns_rcode_noerror;
873 RETERR(process_dhtkey(msg, signer, keyname, &tkeyin,
874 tctx, &tkeyout, ring,
875 &namelist));
876 break;
877 case DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI:
878 tkeyout.error = dns_rcode_noerror;
879 RETERR(process_gsstkey(msg, keyname, &tkeyin, tctx,
880 &tkeyout, ring));
881 break;
882 case DNS_TKEYMODE_DELETE:
883 tkeyout.error = dns_rcode_noerror;
884 RETERR(process_deletetkey(signer, keyname, &tkeyin,
885 &tkeyout, ring));
886 break;
887 case DNS_TKEYMODE_SERVERASSIGNED:
888 case DNS_TKEYMODE_RESOLVERASSIGNED:
889 result = DNS_R_NOTIMP;
890 goto failure;
891 default:
892 tkeyout.error = dns_tsigerror_badmode;
893 }
894
895 failure_with_tkey:
896
897 dns_rdata_init(&rdata);
898 isc_buffer_init(&tkeyoutbuf, tkeyoutdata, sizeof(tkeyoutdata));
899 result = dns_rdata_fromstruct(&rdata, tkeyout.common.rdclass,
900 tkeyout.common.rdtype, &tkeyout,
901 &tkeyoutbuf);
902
903 if (freetkeyin) {
904 dns_rdata_freestruct(&tkeyin);
905 freetkeyin = false;
906 }
907
908 if (tkeyout.key != NULL)
909 isc_mem_put(tkeyout.mctx, tkeyout.key, tkeyout.keylen);
910 if (tkeyout.other != NULL)
911 isc_mem_put(tkeyout.mctx, tkeyout.other, tkeyout.otherlen);
912 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
913 goto failure;
914
915 RETERR(add_rdata_to_list(msg, keyname, &rdata, 0, &namelist));
916
917 RETERR(dns_message_reply(msg, true));
918
919 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(namelist);
920 while (name != NULL) {
921 dns_name_t *next = ISC_LIST_NEXT(name, link);
922 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(namelist, name, link);
923 dns_message_addname(msg, name, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER);
924 name = next;
925 }
926
927 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
928
929 failure:
930
931 if (freetkeyin)
932 dns_rdata_freestruct(&tkeyin);
933 if (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(namelist))
934 free_namelist(msg, &namelist);
935 return (result);
936}
937
938static isc_result_t
939buildquery(dns_message_t *msg, const dns_name_t *name,
940 dns_rdata_tkey_t *tkey, bool win2k)
941{
942 dns_name_t *qname = NULL, *aname = NULL;
943 dns_rdataset_t *question = NULL, *tkeyset = NULL;
944 dns_rdatalist_t *tkeylist = NULL;
945 dns_rdata_t *rdata = NULL;
946 isc_buffer_t *dynbuf = NULL, *anamebuf = NULL, *qnamebuf = NULL;
947 isc_result_t result;
948 unsigned int len;
949
950 REQUIRE(msg != NULL);
951 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
952 REQUIRE(tkey != NULL);
953
954 RETERR(dns_message_gettempname(msg, &qname));
955 RETERR(dns_message_gettempname(msg, &aname));
956
957 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg, &question));
958 dns_rdataset_makequestion(question, dns_rdataclass_any,
959 dns_rdatatype_tkey);
960
961 len = 16 + tkey->algorithm.length + tkey->keylen + tkey->otherlen;
962 RETERR(isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &dynbuf, len));
963 RETERR(isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &anamebuf, name->length));
964 RETERR(isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &qnamebuf, name->length));
965 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdata(msg, &rdata));
966
967 RETERR(dns_rdata_fromstruct(rdata, dns_rdataclass_any,
968 dns_rdatatype_tkey, tkey, dynbuf));
969 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &dynbuf);
970
971 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdatalist(msg, &tkeylist));
972 tkeylist->rdclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
973 tkeylist->type = dns_rdatatype_tkey;
974 ISC_LIST_APPEND(tkeylist->rdata, rdata, link);
975
976 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg, &tkeyset));
977 RETERR(dns_rdatalist_tordataset(tkeylist, tkeyset));
978
979 dns_name_init(qname, NULL);
980 RETERR(dns_name_copy(name, qname, qnamebuf));
981
982 dns_name_init(aname, NULL);
983 RETERR(dns_name_copy(name, aname, anamebuf));
984
985 ISC_LIST_APPEND(qname->list, question, link);
986 ISC_LIST_APPEND(aname->list, tkeyset, link);
987
988 dns_message_addname(msg, qname, DNS_SECTION_QUESTION);
989 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &qnamebuf);
990
991 /*
992 * Windows 2000 needs this in the answer section, not the additional
993 * section where the RFC specifies.
994 */
995 if (win2k)
996 dns_message_addname(msg, aname, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER);
997 else
998 dns_message_addname(msg, aname, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL);
999 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &anamebuf);
1000
1001 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1002
1003 failure:
1004 if (qname != NULL)
1005 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &qname);
1006 if (aname != NULL)
1007 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &aname);
1008 if (question != NULL) {
1009 dns_rdataset_disassociate(question);
1010 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg, &question);
1011 }
1012 if (dynbuf != NULL)
1013 isc_buffer_free(&dynbuf);
1014 if (qnamebuf != NULL)
1015 isc_buffer_free(&qnamebuf);
1016 if (anamebuf != NULL)
1017 isc_buffer_free(&anamebuf);
1018 return (result);
1019}

1021isc_result_t
1022dns_tkey_builddhquery(dns_message_t *msg, dst_key_t *key,
1023 const dns_name_t *name, const dns_name_t *algorithm,
1024 isc_buffer_t *nonce, uint32_t lifetime)
1025{
1026 dns_rdata_tkey_t tkey;
1027 dns_rdata_t *rdata = NULL;
1028 isc_buffer_t *dynbuf = NULL;
1029 isc_region_t r;
1030 dns_name_t keyname;
1031 dns_namelist_t namelist;
1032 isc_result_t result;
1033 isc_stdtime_t now;
1034 dns_name_t *item;
1035
1036 REQUIRE(msg != NULL);
1037 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
1038 REQUIRE(dst_key_alg(key) == DNS_KEYALG_DH);
1039 REQUIRE(dst_key_isprivate(key));
1040 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
1041 REQUIRE(algorithm != NULL);
1042
1043 tkey.common.rdclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1044 tkey.common.rdtype = dns_rdatatype_tkey;
1045 ISC_LINK_INIT(&tkey.common, link);
1046 tkey.mctx = msg->mctx;
1047 dns_name_init(&tkey.algorithm, NULL);
1048 dns_name_clone(algorithm, &tkey.algorithm);
1049 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
1050 tkey.inception = now;
1051 tkey.expire = now + lifetime;
1052 tkey.mode = DNS_TKEYMODE_DIFFIEHELLMAN;
1053 if (nonce != NULL)
1054 isc_buffer_usedregion(nonce, &r);
1055 else {
1056 r.base = NULL;
1057 r.length = 0;
1058 }
1059 tkey.error = 0;
1060 tkey.key = r.base;
1061 tkey.keylen = r.length;
1062 tkey.other = NULL;
1063 tkey.otherlen = 0;
1064
1065 RETERR(buildquery(msg, name, &tkey, false));
1066
1067 RETERR(dns_message_gettemprdata(msg, &rdata));
1068 RETERR(isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &dynbuf, 1024));
1069 RETERR(dst_key_todns(key, dynbuf));
1070 isc_buffer_usedregion(dynbuf, &r);
1071 dns_rdata_fromregion(rdata, dns_rdataclass_any,
1072 dns_rdatatype_key, &r);
1073 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &dynbuf);
1074
1075 dns_name_init(&keyname, NULL);
1076 dns_name_clone(dst_key_name(key), &keyname);
1077
1078 ISC_LIST_INIT(namelist);
1079 RETERR(add_rdata_to_list(msg, &keyname, rdata, 0, &namelist));
1080 item = ISC_LIST_HEAD(namelist);
1081 while (item != NULL) {
1082 dns_name_t *next = ISC_LIST_NEXT(item, link);
1083 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(namelist, item, link);
1084 dns_message_addname(msg, item, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL);
1085 item = next;
1086 }
1087
1088 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1089
1090 failure:
1091
1092 if (dynbuf != NULL)
1093 isc_buffer_free(&dynbuf);
1094 return (result);
1095}

1098dns_tkey_buildgssquery(dns_message_t *msg, const dns_name_t *name,
1099 const dns_name_t *gname,

1103{

1112 REQUIRE(msg != NULL);

1170static isc_result_t
1171find_tkey(dns_message_t *msg, dns_name_t **name, dns_rdata_t *rdata,
1172 int section)
1173{
1174 dns_rdataset_t *tkeyset;
1175 isc_result_t result;
1176
1177 result = dns_message_firstname(msg, section);
1178 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1179 *name = NULL;
1180 dns_message_currentname(msg, section, name);
1181 tkeyset = NULL;
1182 result = dns_message_findtype(*name, dns_rdatatype_tkey, 0,
1183 &tkeyset);
1184 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1185 result = dns_rdataset_first(tkeyset);
1186 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1187 return (result);
1188 dns_rdataset_current(tkeyset, rdata);
1189 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1190 }
1191 result = dns_message_nextname(msg, section);
1192 }
1193 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE)
1194 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
1195 return (result);
1196}
1197
1198isc_result_t
1199dns_tkey_processdhresponse(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
1200 dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *nonce,
1201 dns_tsigkey_t **outkey, dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring)
1202{
1203 dns_rdata_t qtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT, rtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1204 dns_name_t keyname, *tkeyname, *theirkeyname, *ourkeyname, *tempname;
1205 dns_rdataset_t *theirkeyset = NULL, *ourkeyset = NULL;
1206 dns_rdata_t theirkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1207 dst_key_t *theirkey = NULL;
1208 dns_rdata_tkey_t qtkey, rtkey;
1209 unsigned char secretdata[256];
1210 unsigned int sharedsize;
1211 isc_buffer_t *shared = NULL, secret;
1212 isc_region_t r, r2;
1213 isc_result_t result;
1214 bool freertkey = false;
1215
1216 REQUIRE(qmsg != NULL);
1217 REQUIRE(rmsg != NULL);
1218 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
1219 REQUIRE(dst_key_alg(key) == DNS_KEYALG_DH);
1220 REQUIRE(dst_key_isprivate(key));
1221 if (outkey != NULL)
1222 REQUIRE(*outkey == NULL);
1223
1224 if (rmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror)
1225 return (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNSRCODE + rmsg->rcode);
1226 RETERR(find_tkey(rmsg, &tkeyname, &rtkeyrdata, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER));
1227 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&rtkeyrdata, &rtkey, NULL));
1228 freertkey = true;
1229
1230 RETERR(find_tkey(qmsg, &tempname, &qtkeyrdata,
1231 DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL));
1232 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&qtkeyrdata, &qtkey, NULL));
1233
1234 if (rtkey.error != dns_rcode_noerror ||
1235 rtkey.mode != DNS_TKEYMODE_DIFFIEHELLMAN ||
1236 rtkey.mode != qtkey.mode ||
1237 !dns_name_equal(&rtkey.algorithm, &qtkey.algorithm) ||
1238 rmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror) {
1239 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processdhresponse: tkey mode invalid "
1240 "or error set(1)");
1241 result = DNS_R_INVALIDTKEY;
1242 dns_rdata_freestruct(&qtkey);
1243 goto failure;
1244 }
1245
1246 dns_rdata_freestruct(&qtkey);
1247
1248 dns_name_init(&keyname, NULL);
1249 dns_name_clone(dst_key_name(key), &keyname);
1250
1251 ourkeyname = NULL;
1252 ourkeyset = NULL;
1253 RETERR(dns_message_findname(rmsg, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER, &keyname,
1254 dns_rdatatype_key, 0, &ourkeyname,
1255 &ourkeyset));
1256
1257 result = dns_message_firstname(rmsg, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER);
1258 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1259 theirkeyname = NULL;
1260 dns_message_currentname(rmsg, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER,
1261 &theirkeyname);
1262 if (dns_name_equal(theirkeyname, ourkeyname))
1263 goto next;
1264 theirkeyset = NULL;
1265 result = dns_message_findtype(theirkeyname, dns_rdatatype_key,
1266 0, &theirkeyset);
1267 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1268 RETERR(dns_rdataset_first(theirkeyset));
1269 break;
1270 }
1271 next:
1272 result = dns_message_nextname(rmsg, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER);
1273 }
1274
1275 if (theirkeyset == NULL) {
1276 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processdhresponse: failed to find server "
1277 "key");
1278 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
1279 goto failure;
1280 }
1281
1282 dns_rdataset_current(theirkeyset, &theirkeyrdata);
1283 RETERR(dns_dnssec_keyfromrdata(theirkeyname, &theirkeyrdata,
1284 rmsg->mctx, &theirkey));
1285
1286 RETERR(dst_key_secretsize(key, &sharedsize));
1287 RETERR(isc_buffer_allocate(rmsg->mctx, &shared, sharedsize));
1288
1289 RETERR(dst_key_computesecret(theirkey, key, shared));
1290
1291 isc_buffer_init(&secret, secretdata, sizeof(secretdata));
1292
1293 r.base = rtkey.key;
1294 r.length = rtkey.keylen;
1295 if (nonce != NULL)
1296 isc_buffer_usedregion(nonce, &r2);
1297 else {
1298 r2.base = NULL;
1299 r2.length = 0;
1300 }
1301 RETERR(compute_secret(shared, &r2, &r, &secret));
1302
1303 isc_buffer_usedregion(&secret, &r);
1304 result = dns_tsigkey_create(tkeyname, &rtkey.algorithm,
1305 r.base, r.length, true,
1306 NULL, rtkey.inception, rtkey.expire,
1307 rmsg->mctx, ring, outkey);
1308 isc_buffer_free(&shared);
1309 dns_rdata_freestruct(&rtkey);
1310 dst_key_free(&theirkey);
1311 return (result);
1312
1313 failure:
1314 if (shared != NULL)
1315 isc_buffer_free(&shared);
1316
1317 if (theirkey != NULL)
1318 dst_key_free(&theirkey);
1319
1320 if (freertkey)
1321 dns_rdata_freestruct(&rtkey);
1322
1323 return (result);
1324}

1326isc_result_t
1327dns_tkey_processgssresponse(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
1328 const dns_name_t *gname, gss_ctx_id_t *context,
1329 isc_buffer_t *outtoken, dns_tsigkey_t **outkey,
1330 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring, char **err_message)
1331{
1332 dns_rdata_t rtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT, qtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1333 dns_name_t *tkeyname;
1334 dns_rdata_tkey_t rtkey, qtkey;
1335 dst_key_t *dstkey = NULL;
1336 isc_buffer_t intoken;
1337 isc_result_t result;
1338 unsigned char array[TEMP_BUFFER_SZ];
1339
1340 REQUIRE(outtoken != NULL);
1341 REQUIRE(qmsg != NULL);
1342 REQUIRE(rmsg != NULL);
1343 REQUIRE(gname != NULL);
1344 REQUIRE(ring != NULL);
1345 if (outkey != NULL)
1346 REQUIRE(*outkey == NULL);
1347
1348 if (rmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror)
1349 return (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNSRCODE + rmsg->rcode);
1350 RETERR(find_tkey(rmsg, &tkeyname, &rtkeyrdata, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER));
1351 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&rtkeyrdata, &rtkey, NULL));
1352
1353 /*
1354 * Win2k puts the item in the ANSWER section, while the RFC
1355 * specifies it should be in the ADDITIONAL section. Check first
1356 * where it should be, and then where it may be.
1357 */
1358 result = find_tkey(qmsg, &tkeyname, &qtkeyrdata,
1359 DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL);
1360 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
1361 result = find_tkey(qmsg, &tkeyname, &qtkeyrdata,
1362 DNS_SECTION_ANSWER);
1363 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1364 goto failure;
1365
1366 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&qtkeyrdata, &qtkey, NULL));
1367
1368 if (rtkey.error != dns_rcode_noerror ||
1369 rtkey.mode != DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI ||
1370 !dns_name_equal(&rtkey.algorithm, &qtkey.algorithm)) {
1371 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processgssresponse: tkey mode invalid "
1372 "or error set(2) %d", rtkey.error);
1373 dumpmessage(qmsg);
1374 dumpmessage(rmsg);
1375 result = DNS_R_INVALIDTKEY;
1376 goto failure;
1377 }
1378
1379 isc_buffer_init(outtoken, array, sizeof(array));
1380 isc_buffer_init(&intoken, rtkey.key, rtkey.keylen);
1381 RETERR(dst_gssapi_initctx(gname, &intoken, outtoken, context,
1382 ring->mctx, err_message));
1383
1384 RETERR(dst_key_fromgssapi(dns_rootname, *context, rmsg->mctx,
1385 &dstkey, NULL));
1386
1387 RETERR(dns_tsigkey_createfromkey(tkeyname, DNS_TSIG_GSSAPI_NAME,
1388 dstkey, false, NULL,
1389 rtkey.inception, rtkey.expire,
1390 ring->mctx, ring, outkey));
1391 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
1392 dns_rdata_freestruct(&rtkey);
1393 return (result);
1394
1395 failure:
1396 /*
1397 * XXXSRA This probably leaks memory from rtkey and qtkey.
1398 */
1399 if (dstkey != NULL)
1400 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
1401 return (result);
1402}

1404isc_result_t
1405dns_tkey_processdeleteresponse(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
1406 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring)
1407{
1408 dns_rdata_t qtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT, rtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1409 dns_name_t *tkeyname, *tempname;
1410 dns_rdata_tkey_t qtkey, rtkey;
1411 dns_tsigkey_t *tsigkey = NULL;
1412 isc_result_t result;
1413
1414 REQUIRE(qmsg != NULL);
1415 REQUIRE(rmsg != NULL);
1416
1417 if (rmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror)
1418 return(ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNSRCODE + rmsg->rcode);
1419
1420 RETERR(find_tkey(rmsg, &tkeyname, &rtkeyrdata, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER));
1421 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&rtkeyrdata, &rtkey, NULL));
1422
1423 RETERR(find_tkey(qmsg, &tempname, &qtkeyrdata,
1424 DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL));
1425 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&qtkeyrdata, &qtkey, NULL));
1426
1427 if (rtkey.error != dns_rcode_noerror ||
1428 rtkey.mode != DNS_TKEYMODE_DELETE ||
1429 rtkey.mode != qtkey.mode ||
1430 !dns_name_equal(&rtkey.algorithm, &qtkey.algorithm) ||
1431 rmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror) {
1432 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processdeleteresponse: tkey mode invalid "
1433 "or error set(3)");
1434 result = DNS_R_INVALIDTKEY;
1435 dns_rdata_freestruct(&qtkey);
1436 dns_rdata_freestruct(&rtkey);
1437 goto failure;
1438 }
1439
1440 dns_rdata_freestruct(&qtkey);
1441
1442 RETERR(dns_tsigkey_find(&tsigkey, tkeyname, &rtkey.algorithm, ring));
1443
1444 dns_rdata_freestruct(&rtkey);
1445
1446 /*
1447 * Mark the key as deleted.
1448 */
1449 dns_tsigkey_setdeleted(tsigkey);
1450 /*
1451 * Release the reference.
1452 */
1453 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
1454
1455 failure:
1456 return (result);
1457}

1459isc_result_t
1460dns_tkey_gssnegotiate(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
1461 const dns_name_t *server, gss_ctx_id_t *context,
1462 dns_tsigkey_t **outkey, dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring,
1463 bool win2k, char **err_message)
1464{
1465 dns_rdata_t rtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT, qtkeyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1466 dns_name_t *tkeyname;
1467 dns_rdata_tkey_t rtkey, qtkey, tkey;
1468 isc_buffer_t intoken, outtoken;
1469 dst_key_t *dstkey = NULL;
1470 isc_result_t result;
1471 unsigned char array[TEMP_BUFFER_SZ];
1472 bool freertkey = false;
1473
1474 REQUIRE(qmsg != NULL);
1475 REQUIRE(rmsg != NULL);
1476 REQUIRE(server != NULL);
1477 if (outkey != NULL)
1478 REQUIRE(*outkey == NULL);
1479
1480 if (rmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror)
1481 return (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNSRCODE + rmsg->rcode);
1482
1483 RETERR(find_tkey(rmsg, &tkeyname, &rtkeyrdata, DNS_SECTION_ANSWER));
1484 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&rtkeyrdata, &rtkey, NULL));
1485 freertkey = true;
1486
1487 if (win2k == true)
1488 RETERR(find_tkey(qmsg, &tkeyname, &qtkeyrdata,
1489 DNS_SECTION_ANSWER));
1490 else
1491 RETERR(find_tkey(qmsg, &tkeyname, &qtkeyrdata,
1492 DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL));
1493
1494 RETERR(dns_rdata_tostruct(&qtkeyrdata, &qtkey, NULL));
1495
1496 if (rtkey.error != dns_rcode_noerror ||
1497 rtkey.mode != DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI ||
1498 !dns_name_equal(&rtkey.algorithm, &qtkey.algorithm))
1499 {
1500 tkey_log("dns_tkey_processdhresponse: tkey mode invalid "
1501 "or error set(4)");
1502 result = DNS_R_INVALIDTKEY;
1503 goto failure;
1504 }
1505
1506 isc_buffer_init(&intoken, rtkey.key, rtkey.keylen);
1507 isc_buffer_init(&outtoken, array, sizeof(array));
1508
1509 result = dst_gssapi_initctx(server, &intoken, &outtoken, context,
1510 ring->mctx, err_message);
1511 if (result != DNS_R_CONTINUE && result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1512 return (result);
1513
1514 if (result == DNS_R_CONTINUE) {
1515 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
1516
1517 dns_fixedname_init(&fixed);
1518 dns_name_copy(tkeyname, dns_fixedname_name(&fixed), NULL);
1519 tkeyname = dns_fixedname_name(&fixed);
1520
1521 tkey.common.rdclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1522 tkey.common.rdtype = dns_rdatatype_tkey;
1523 ISC_LINK_INIT(&tkey.common, link);
1524 tkey.mctx = NULL;
1525 dns_name_init(&tkey.algorithm, NULL);
1526
1527 if (win2k)
1528 dns_name_clone(DNS_TSIG_GSSAPIMS_NAME, &tkey.algorithm);
1529 else
1530 dns_name_clone(DNS_TSIG_GSSAPI_NAME, &tkey.algorithm);
1531
1532 tkey.inception = qtkey.inception;
1533 tkey.expire = qtkey.expire;
1534 tkey.mode = DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI;
1535 tkey.error = 0;
1536 tkey.key = isc_buffer_base(&outtoken);
1537 tkey.keylen = isc_buffer_usedlength(&outtoken);
1538 tkey.other = NULL;
1539 tkey.otherlen = 0;
1540
1541 dns_message_reset(qmsg, DNS_MESSAGE_INTENTRENDER);
1542 RETERR(buildquery(qmsg, tkeyname, &tkey, win2k));
1543 return (DNS_R_CONTINUE);
1544 }
1545
1546 RETERR(dst_key_fromgssapi(dns_rootname, *context, rmsg->mctx,
1547 &dstkey, NULL));
1548
1549 /*
1550 * XXXSRA This seems confused. If we got CONTINUE from initctx,
1551 * the GSS negotiation hasn't completed yet, so we can't sign
1552 * anything yet.
1553 */
1554
1555 RETERR(dns_tsigkey_createfromkey(tkeyname,
1556 (win2k
1557 ? DNS_TSIG_GSSAPIMS_NAME
1558 : DNS_TSIG_GSSAPI_NAME),
1559 dstkey, true, NULL,
1560 rtkey.inception, rtkey.expire,
1561 ring->mctx, ring, outkey));
1562 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
1563 dns_rdata_freestruct(&rtkey);
1564 return (result);
1565
1566 failure:
1567 /*
1568 * XXXSRA This probably leaks memory from qtkey.
1569 */
1570 if (freertkey)
1571 dns_rdata_freestruct(&rtkey);
1572 if (dstkey != NULL)
1573 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
1574 return (result);
1575}
